quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  36,55,"Indeed this day the dwellers of Paradise are in comfort, with blissful hearts."
  36,56,"They and their wives are in shades, reclining on thrones."
  36,57,"In it (paradise) are fruits for them and whatever they ask for."
  36,58,"Upon them will be “Peace” – a Word from their Merciful Lord!"
  36,59,"“And be separated (from others) this day, O you criminals!”"
  36,60,"“O Descendants of Adam! Did I not take a covenant from you that you shall not worship the devil? Undoubtedly, he is your open enemy.”"
  36,61,"“And that you shall worship Me? This is the Straight Path.”"
  36,62,"“And he has indeed led a large number of you astray; so did you not have sense?”"
  36,63,"“This is hell, which you were promised.”"
  36,64,"“Enter it this day – the recompense of your disbelief.”"
  36,65,"This day We will set a seal on their mouths, and their hands will speak out to Us and their feet will bear witness to their deeds."
  36,66,"And had We willed, We could have quenched their eyes so they would rush towards the path, unable to see a thing."
  36,67,"And had We willed, We could have disfigured their faces while they were in their homes, therefore unable to go forward or turn back."
  36,68,"And whomever We bring to an old age, We reverse him in creation; so do they not understand?"
  36,69,"And We have not taught him (Prophet Mohammed- peace and blessings be upon him) to recite poetry, nor does it befit him; it is nothing but an advice and the bright Qur’an."
  36,70,"To warn the living*, and to prove the Word against disbelievers. (Only the believers are deemed alive in Allah’s sight.)"
